    "main_text": "Understand major food allergens, their impact, and how to manage them in food preparation.",
    "section_1_title": "Introduction",
    "section_1_content": "Allergens are substances that can cause allergic reactions in some individuals. Proper identification is crucial for safe food service.",
    "section_2_title": "Common Allergens",
    "section_2_content": "Common allergens include milk, eggs, fish, shellfish, tree nuts, peanuts, wheat, soy, and sesame.",
    "section_3_title": "Cross-Contact Risks",
    "section_3_content": "Cross-contact occurs when allergens are unintentionally transferred from one food to another. Proper handling can minimize this risk."
